## US-130 Complete

**Files created:**
- `config/game/ambientAudio.json` — biome layer volumes + time gate config
- `game/systems/ambientAudio.ts` — ambient audio system
- `game/systems/ambientAudio.test.ts` — 31 tests

**Acceptance criteria verified:**
- [x] `game/systems/ambientAudio.ts` exists
- [x] 6-layer ambient per biome (wind/birds/insects/crickets/water/vegetation)
- [x] `AmbientZoneComponent` entities drive the mix via `ZoneInput` / `computeAmbientMix`
- [x] Crossfade by distance — linear falloff `volume * (1 - dist/radius)` in XZ plane
- [x] Biome-specific audio plays — `layersForBiome()` reads per-biome weights from config
- [x] `npx tsc --noEmit` → 0 errors
- [x] `npx jest --no-coverage` → 3110/3110 pass

`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The key architecture decision: **6 global layer accumulators** rather than per-zone synthesis nodes. Each zone contributes weighted volumes to the global channels each frame. This is O(zones × layers) per tick — cheap and scalable. The injected `nodeFactory` in `initAmbientLayers` makes the runtime Tone.js layer management fully mockable without pulling in the actual AudioContext.
